<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>9 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RT-8609 SERIES - REMOVE - AUXILIARY SECTION</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="3">
        <title>AUXILIARY SECTION</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the bolts that attach the two sections (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302926">Figure 26</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302926" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302926" filename="../figg13/G1302926.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 26. Remove Bolts Attaching Sections</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>There are two lengths of bolts; note their location.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Insert the three bolts in the tapped holes of the housing flange. Tighten evenly to move
                auxiliary section to the rear and just far enough from the front section to break the gasket seal (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302927">Figure 27</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302927" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302927" filename="../figg13/G1302927.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 27. Tighten Bolts Evenly to Move Auxiliary Section to Rear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the bolts and attach a chain hoist to the auxiliary section (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302928">Figure 28</hotlnk>). Move the assembly to the rear until free of the front
                section and remove the gasket.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302928" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302928" filename="../figg13/G1302928.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 28. Attach Hoist to Auxiliary Section</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
